236 lbs vs 143 lbs. 
My god it's still like looking at the photos on the left wasn't even me. I spent years being so embarrassed vs proud of my journey. Even to this day when my friends bring up this Instagram to new people I don't know I get embarrassed. I also get embarrassed of my loose skin and cellulite and wish that I never put my body through such damage. There's absolutely nothing I can do about the past, but there's a hell of a lot I can do in the future. I've been stagnant for so long. I've become so comfortable with myself I've learned to make "loving myself how I am" an excuse. I do love myself now, but I need to stop letting that be an excuse to move forward and hit new goals. It's been my goal to hit my 100 lbs lost mark for over a year now and I've been within 10 lbs of hitting that for a year. A YEAR. People ask me about plateaus, well this has been mine. I am going to be 136 or under by July 1st. I am making this a promise to myself. I will be really disappointed if I let myself go any longer. I need to be accountable for my goals starting today. I'm going to update you guys every day from now until July 1st.
